				<p>Because Isaiah is quoted so extensively, he deserves mention as one of the major contributors to the Book of Mormon. A useful footnote to 2 Nephi 12:2 [<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/12.2?lang=eng#1" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">2 Ne. 12:2</a>] in the current English edition of the LDS scriptures indicates that some 433 verses of Isaiah&mdash;roughly a third of the entire book&mdash;are quoted in the Book of Mormon. In the English language edition, more than half (about 233 verses) differ in some detail from their biblical counterpart, &ldquo;while about 200 verses have the same wording as KJV.&rdquo; One scholar of Isaiah documents that no less than 391 of the verses refer to the attributes, appearance, majesty, and mission of Jesus Christ (see Monte S. Nyman, <span class="emphasis">&ldquo;Great Are the Words of Isaiah&rdquo;</span> [1980], 7, 283&ndash;87).  Elder Jeffrey R. Holland (<span class="emphasis">Christ and the New Covenant: The Messianic Message of the Book of Mormon</span> [1997], 78&ndash;94) has classified the teachings of Isaiah as recorded in the Book of Mormon into five topical categories:  (1) Christ&rsquo;s Birth and Mortal Ministry (see <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/11.13,15,18,20?lang=eng#12" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">1 Ne. 11:13, 15, 18, 20</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/17.14-15?lang=eng#13" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">2 Ne. 17:14&ndash;15</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/7.10?lang=eng#9" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Alma 7:10</a>).  (2) Christ Visits the Spirits in Prison (see <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/21.6-9?lang=eng#5" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">1 Ne. 21:6&ndash;9</a>).  (3) Christ Shows Kindness to and Preserves Zion in the Last Days (see <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/1-ne/21.13-16?lang=eng#12" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">1 Ne. 21:13&ndash;16</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/7.1-2?lang=eng#0" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">2 Ne. 7:1&ndash;2</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/22.8?lang=eng#7" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">3 Ne. 22:8</a>&mdash;quoting from <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/ot/isa/54.8?lang=eng#7" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Isa. 54:8</a>).  (4) The Millennial Christ (see <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/12.2-5?lang=eng#1" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">2 Ne. 12:2&ndash;5</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/21.1-12?lang=eng#0" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">2 Ne. 21:1&ndash;12</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/30.9?lang=eng#8" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">2 Ne. 30:9</a>).  (5) The Crucifixion and Atonement (see <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/mosiah/14.1-12?lang=eng#0" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Mosiah 14:1&ndash;12</a>).</p>
