      </span>
				<p>See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/rom/5.11?lang=eng#10" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Rom. 5:11</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-99911_000_028"><a name="-99911_000_028">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote24-99911_000_028">24.</a>
      </span>
				<p><span class="emphasis">Atonement:</span> 28 times; <span class="emphasis">atone, atoning,</span> or <span class="emphasis">atoned:</span> 8 times; plus <span class="emphasis">atoneth:</span> 3 times; equals 39 times. Within several verses, the word <span class="emphasis">atonement</span> appears more than once (see <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/9.7?lang=eng#6" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">2 Ne. 9:7</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/34.9?lang=eng#8" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Alma 34:9</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/alma/42.23?lang=eng#22" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Alma 42:23</a>).</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-99911_000_028"><a name="-99911_000_028">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote25-99911_000_028">25.</a>
      </span>
				<p>The word <span class="emphasis">resurrection</span> appears 41 times in the King James Version of the Bible; it appears 81 times in the Book of Mormon (see also <span class="emphasis">Christ and the New Covenant,</span> 238).</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-99911_000_028"><a name="-99911_000_028">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote26-99911_000_028">26.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/84.57?lang=eng#56" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 84:57</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-99911_000_028"><a name="-99911_000_028">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote27-99911_000_028">27.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/21.1?lang=eng#0" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">3 Ne. 21:1</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/29.title?lang=eng" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">3 Ne. 29</a>: chapter heading.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-99911_000_028"><a name="-99911_000_028">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote28-99911_000_028">28.</a>
      </span>
				<p><span class="emphasis">Covenant</span> comes from the Latin <span class="emphasis">convenire,</span> which means &ldquo;to come with,&rdquo; &ldquo;to agree.&rdquo;</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-99911_000_028"><a name="-99911_000_028">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote29-99911_000_028">29.</a>
      </span>
				<p><span class="emphasis">Testament</span> comes from the Latin <span class="emphasis">testis,</span> which means &ldquo;witness.&rdquo; <span class="emphasis">Testament</span> is also related to the Latin roots <span class="emphasis">tres </span>and<span class="emphasis"> stare, </span>which mean &ldquo;three stand.&rdquo;</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-99911_000_028"><a name="-99911_000_028">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote30-99911_000_028">30.</a>
      </span>
				<p><span class="emphasis">Witness</span> comes from the Old English <span class="emphasis">wit,</span> which means &ldquo;knowledge.&rdquo; A witness is defined as one who has special knowledge.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-99911_000_028"><a name="-99911_000_028">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote31-99911_000_028">31.</a>
      </span>
				<p>Jeffrey R. Holland, <span class="emphasis">Christ and the New Covenant,</span> 9&ndash;10.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-99911_000_028"><a name="-99911_000_028">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote32-99911_000_028">32.</a>
      </span>
				<p><span class="emphasis">History of the Church,</span> 4:461.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-99911_000_028"><a name="-99911_000_028">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote33-99911_000_028">33.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/17.6?lang=eng#5" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 17:6</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-99911_000_028"><a name="-99911_000_028">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote34-99911_000_028">34.</a>
      </span>
				<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/9.15-16,18,20-22?lang=eng#14" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">3 Ne. 9:15&ndash;16, 18, 20&ndash;22</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-99911_000_028"><a name="-99911_000_028">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote35-99911_000_028">35.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/11.14?lang=eng#13" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">3 Ne. 11:14</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-99911_000_028"><a name="-99911_000_028">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote36-99911_000_028">36.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/15.9?lang=eng#8" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">3 Ne. 15:9</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-99911_000_028"><a name="-99911_000_028">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote37-99911_000_028">37.</a>
      </span>
				<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/26.27?lang=eng#26" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">2 Ne. 26:27</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-99911_000_028"><a name="-99911_000_028">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote38-99911_000_028">38.</a>
      </span>
				<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/2-ne/26.33?lang=eng#32" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">2 Ne. 26:33</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-99911_000_028"><a name="-99911_000_028">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote39-99911_000_028">39.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See <span class="emphasis">Christ and the New Covenant,</span> 349.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-99911_000_028"><a name="-99911_000_028">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote40-99911_000_028">40.</a>
      </span>
				<p>From 7 April to 30 June 1829. After subtracting time spent for other contemporary tasks, working time available was closer to 55 days. The present edition of the Book of Mormon contains 531 pages. Assuming 55 days for the work of translation, the rate is calculated as 9.7 present-day pages per day.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-99911_000_028"><a name="-99911_000_028">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote41-99911_000_028">41.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See John W. Welch and Tim Rathbone, &ldquo;Book of Mormon Translation by Joseph Smith,&rdquo; <span class="emphasis">Encyclopedia of Mormonism,</span> 4 vols. [1992], 1:211.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-99911_000_028"><a name="-99911_000_028">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote42-99911_000_028">42.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See &ldquo;A Chronology of Church History,&rdquo; Appendix 2,<span class="emphasis"> Encyclopedia of Mormonism,</span> 4:1652, date of 11 June 1829.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-99911_000_028"><a name="-99911_000_028">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote43-99911_000_028">43.</a>
      </span>
				<p>Sections 6&ndash;9 and 11&ndash;18.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-99911_000_028"><a name="-99911_000_028">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote44-99911_000_028">44.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/moro/10.4-5?lang=eng#3" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Moro. 10:4&ndash;5</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-99911_000_028"><a name="-99911_000_028">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote45-99911_000_028">45.</a>
      </span>
				<p>The Prophet Joseph Smith declared that &ldquo;a man would get nearer to God by abiding by its [the Book of Mormon&rsquo;s] precepts, than by any other book&rdquo; (<span class="emphasis">History of the Church,</span> 4:461).</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-99911_000_028"><a name="-99911_000_028">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote46-99911_000_028">46.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/matt/14.19-20?lang=eng#18" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Matt. 14:19&ndash;20</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/mark/6.41-42?lang=eng#40" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Mark 6:41&ndash;42</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/luke/9.16-17?lang=eng#15" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Luke 9:16&ndash;17</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-99911_000_028"><a name="-99911_000_028">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote47-99911_000_028">47.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/matt/11.5?lang=eng#4" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Matt. 11:5</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/luke/7.21-22?lang=eng#20" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Luke 7:21&ndash;22</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-99911_000_028"><a name="-99911_000_028">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote48-99911_000_028">48.</a>
      </span>
				<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/20.14?lang=eng#13" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 20:14</a>.</p>
			</li>
		</ol>
                                        
